{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0188qX8Pcw9aB77tKu6rvvYu","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Implementation History — 203-e2e-integration\n     2→\n     3→Iteration log for the autonomous spec loop. Each entry records what was\n     4→attempted and whether it succeeded. The agent reads this file at the start\n     5→of every iteration to understand prior context.\n     6→\n     7→---\n     8→\n     9→## Iteration 1 — Local E2E Playwright config + directory\n    10→\n    11→**Item**: Add dedicated local E2E Playwright project/config (`e2e/local/**`)\n    12→\n    13→**Changes**:\n    14→- Created `apps/platform/playwright.local.config.ts` — new config for local E2E tests (port 3002, `VITE_MOCK_MODE=false`, `VITE_RPC_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8899`)\n    15→- Updated `apps/platform/playwright.config.ts` — added `testMatch: \"visual/**/*.spec.ts\"` to prevent default config from running local tests\n    16→- Created `apps/platform/e2e/local/smoke.spec.ts` — smoke test verifying app loads in real mode\n    17→- Added `test:e2e:local` script to `apps/platform/package.json`\n    18→\n    19→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` (0 errors) + `pnpm typecheck` (pass) — all green.\n    20→\n    21→## Iteration 1 — 2026-02-26T10:52:11Z — OK\n    22→- **Log**: iteration-001.log\n    23→\n    24→## Iteration 2 — Localnet bootstrap script\n    25→\n    26→**Item**: Create localnet bootstrap script: start fresh `solana-test-validator`, deploy coinflip + platform programs, wait for RPC readiness\n    27→\n    28→**Changes**:\n    29→- Created `apps/platform/scripts/localnet-bootstrap.sh` — starts fresh `solana-test-validator` with programs preloaded via `--bpf-program`, waits for RPC readiness, writes PID file for teardown\n    30→- Updated `.devcontainer/devcontainer.json` — added `--security-opt=seccomp=unconfined` to `runArgs` (required for Solana 3.x io_uring)\n    31→- Updated `.gitignore` — added `.localnet-ledger/` and `.localnet.pid`\n    32→\n    33→**Key design decisions**:\n    34→- Uses `--bpf-program` to preload programs at genesis (faster than post-start deploy)\n    35→- Writes PID to `.localnet.pid` for teardown script to consume\n    36→- Includes io_uring preflight check with clear error message pointing to seccomp fix\n    37→- Kills any existing validator (by PID file or port 8899) before starting fresh\n    38→\n    39→**Note**: `solana-test-validator` requires `io_uring` syscall (Solana 3.x). Docker blocks it by default. The devcontainer fix (`seccomp=unconfined`) requires container rebuild to take effect. Script cannot be fully tested in the current session but syntax validates (`bash -n`) and all logic is sound.\n    40→\n    41→**Verification**: `bash -n` (syntax OK) + `pnpm lint` (0 errors) — all green.\n    42→\n    43→## Iteration 2 — 2026-02-26T11:00:00Z — OK\n    44→- **Log**: iteration-002.log\n    45→\n    46→## Iteration 3 — Localnet teardown script\n    47→\n    48→**Item**: Create localnet teardown script: stop validator process, clean temp ledger/logs, and guarantee cleanup on test failure\n    49→\n    50→**Changes**:\n    51→- Created `apps/platform/scripts/localnet-teardown.sh` — counterpart to `localnet-bootstrap.sh`\n    52→  - Reads PID from `.localnet.pid` and sends SIGTERM, waits up to 5s, then SIGKILL if needed\n    53→  - Kills any stray process on port 8899 (safety net)\n    54→  - Removes `.localnet-ledger/` directory and `.localnet-validator.log`\n    55→  - `--keep-logs` flag to preserve log file for debugging\n    56→  - Idempotent: safe to call multiple times or when nothing is running\n    57→\n    58→**Verification**: `bash -n` (syntax OK) + `pnpm lint` (0 errors) — all green.\n    59→\n    60→## Iteration 3 — 2026-02-26T11:10:00Z — OK\n    61→- **Log**: iteration-003.log\n    62→\n    63→## Iteration 3 — 2026-02-26T11:01:27Z — OK\n    64→- **Log**: iteration-003.log\n    65→\n    66→## Iteration 4 — Deterministic wallet-funding helper\n    67→\n    68→**Item**: Add deterministic wallet-funding helper (airdrop + confirm) for both test players before each local suite run\n    69→\n    70→**Changes**:\n    71→- Created `apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/wallets.ts` — wallet funding helper for local E2E tests\n    72→  - Deterministic keypairs: `PLAYER_A` (seed 0xaa×32) and `PLAYER_B` (seed 0xbb×32) via `Keypair.fromSeed()`\n    73→  - `fundWallet(connection, pubkey, sol)` — airdrops SOL and confirms transaction\n    74→  - `fundTestWallets(rpcUrl, sol)` — funds both players in parallel, sanity-checks balances\n    75→  - Default: 10 SOL per player on `http://127.0.0.1:8899`\n    76→\n    77→**Design decisions**:\n    78→- Fixed seeds (not random) ensure identical keypairs across runs for determinism\n    79→- Parallel airdrop via `Promise.all` for faster setup\n    80→- Post-airdrop balance assertions catch silent RPC failures early\n    81→- Helper is importable from any test file (`beforeAll` or global setup)\n    82→\n    83→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` (0 errors) + `pnpm typecheck` (pass) — all green.\n    84→\n    85→## Iteration 4 — 2026-02-26T11:05:14Z — OK\n    86→- **Log**: iteration-004.log\n    87→\n    88→## Iteration 5 — Shared E2E page-object helpers\n    89→\n    90→**Item**: Add shared E2E helpers: selectors/page-object methods for create, join, claim, cancel, and reusable wait/assert primitives\n    91→\n    92→**Changes**:\n    93→- Created `apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/page-objects.ts` — comprehensive E2E helper module\n    94→  - `sel` object: CSS-class-based selectors for all coinflip UI elements (sidebar, lobby, match cards, active match, results, errors)\n    95→  - Page-object actions: `navigateToCoinflip()`, `selectTier()`, `selectSide()`, `createMatch()`, `joinMatch()`, `cancelMatch()`, `claimOrSettle()`, `backToLobby()`\n    96→  - Wait primitives: `waitForPhaseLabel()`, `waitForResult()`, `waitForLobbyMatch()`, `waitForLobby()`, `waitForText()`\n    97→  - Assert primitives: `assertLobbyEmpty()`, `assertErrorToast()`, `assertNoErrorToast()`\n    98→  - Utility: `getSolBalance()` (RPC-based, via page.evaluate), `trackConsoleErrors()` (collector + assertClean)\n    99→\n   100→**Design decisions**:\n   101→- CSS-class selectors (no data-testid needed — matches existing component markup)\n   102→- All actions include built-in waits for state transitions (e.g., createMatch waits for active match view)\n   103→- `claimOrSettle()` handles both winner (Claim Payout) and loser (Settle & Return) since both use the sidebar button\n   104→- `getSolBalance()` uses page.evaluate + JSON-RPC for balance checks from within test context\n   105→- `trackConsoleErrors()` filters known browser noise (favicon, fonts, third-party cookies)\n   106→\n   107→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` (0 errors) + `pnpm typecheck` (pass) — all green.\n   108→\n   109→## Iteration 5 — 2026-02-26T11:15:00Z — OK\n   110→- **Log**: iteration-005.log\n   111→\n   112→## Iteration 5 — 2026-02-26T11:09:56Z — OK\n   113→- **Log**: iteration-005.log\n   114→\n   115→## Iteration 6 — Shared on-chain assertion helpers\n   116→\n   117→**Item**: Add shared on-chain assertion helpers for match PDA state, treasury fee delta, and player profile stat updates\n   118→\n   119→**Changes**:\n   120→- Created `apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/on-chain.ts` — comprehensive on-chain assertion module\n   121→  - PDA derivation: `getMatchPda()`, `getConfigPda()`, `getPlayerProfilePda()`\n   122→  - Program instances: `getCoinflipProgram()`, `getPlatformProgram()` (read-only Anchor providers)\n   123→  - Fetch helpers: `fetchMatch()`, `fetchPlayerProfile()`, `getTreasuryAddress()`\n   124→  - Balance helpers: `getBalanceLamports()`, `snapshotBalance()`\n   125→  - Fee calculation: `calculateExpectedFee()` — mirrors on-chain floor(pool * 300 / 10000) logic\n   126→  - Match assertions: `assertMatchCreated()` (verifies waiting phase, creator, tier, side), `assertMatchClosed()` (verifies PDA no longer exists)\n   127→  - Treasury assertions: `assertTreasuryFee()` — compares balance delta against expected fee\n   128→  - Profile assertions: `assertPlayerProfile()`, `assertPlayerProfileDelta()`, `snapshotPlayerProfile()`\n   129→\n   130→**Design decisions**:\n   131→- Uses `@rng-utopia/anchor-client` IDLs for account deserialization (same as production code)\n   132→- Program IDs derived from IDL `.address` field (single source of truth)\n   133→- Read-only AnchorProvider with empty wallet (no signing needed for queries)\n   134→- Snapshot/delta pattern for treasury and profile assertions (capture before, assert delta after)\n   135→- Null-safe fetches: returns null for closed/missing accounts instead of throwing\n   136→- TypeScript interfaces for MatchAccount and PlayerProfileAccount mirror on-chain struct shapes\n   137→\n   138→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` (0 errors) + `pnpm typecheck` (pass) — all green.\n   139→\n   140→## Iteration 6 — 2026-02-26T11:15:31Z — OK\n   141→- **Log**: iteration-006.log\n   142→\n   143→## Iteration 7 — Dual-browser-context fixture\n   144→\n   145→**Item**: Add dual-browser-context fixture with isolated storage/session for player A and player B\n   146→\n   147→**Changes**:\n   148→- Created `packages/wallet/src/test/TestWalletWrapper.tsx` — bridge component that reads a 32-byte seed from `window.__TEST_WALLET_SEED__` and renders `TestWalletProvider` with the corresponding `Keypair`\n   149→- Modified `packages/wallet/src/WalletProvider.tsx` — added test wallet mode:\n   150→  - New `isTestWalletMode()` function checks `VITE_TEST_WALLET` env var\n   151→  - Lazy-loads `TestWalletWrapper` when `VITE_TEST_WALLET=true`\n   152→  - Mode priority: mock > test > real\n   153→- Created `apps/platform/e2e/local/fixtures.ts` — dual-browser-context Playwright fixture:\n   154→  - `playerAContext` / `playerBContext`: isolated browser contexts with keypair seed injected via `addInitScript`\n   155→  - `playerAPage` / `playerBPage`: ready-to-use Page instances within each context\n   156→  - `playerAKeypair` / `playerBKeypair`: deterministic keypairs from `wallets.ts`\n   157→  - `connection`: shared RPC connection to the local validator\n   158→  - Exports extended `test` and `expect` for use in lifecycle tests\n   159→- Updated `apps/platform/playwright.local.config.ts` — added `VITE_TEST_WALLET: \"true\"` env var\n   160→\n   161→**Design decisions**:\n   162→- Keypair injection via `context.addInitScript()` runs before any page script, ensuring the seed is available when React renders `WalletProvider`\n   163→- `TestWalletWrapper` is lazy-loaded to keep the bundle clean in non-test modes\n   164→- Each context is fully isolated (separate storage, cookies, sessions) — no cross-contamination between players\n   165→- The `createPlayerContext()` helper extracts the 32-byte seed from `keypair.secretKey.slice(0, 32)` and passes it as a plain array (serialisable across the Playwright boundary)\n   166→\n   167→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` (0 errors) + `pnpm typecheck` (pass) — all green.\n   168→\n   169→## Iteration 7 — 2026-02-26T11:25:00Z — OK\n   170→- **Log**: iteration-007.log\n   171→\n   172→## Iteration 7 — 2026-02-26T11:22:53Z — OK\n   173→- **Log**: iteration-007.log\n   174→\n   175→## Iteration 8 — Local lifecycle test (create → join → resolve → claim)\n   176→\n   177→**Item**: Implement local lifecycle test (create -> join -> resolve programmatically -> claim) with UI assertions in both contexts\n   178→\n   179→**Changes**:\n   180→- Created `apps/platform/scripts/localnet-accounts/orao-network-state.json` — mock Orao VRF network state PDA with deterministic treasury address at offset 40 (required by `buildJoinMatchTx`)\n   181→- Created `apps/platform/scripts/localnet-accounts/orao-random-player-a.json` — pre-fulfilled mock VRF randomness account for Player A's match PDA (byte[0]=2→HEADS, byte[8]=2→frontend fulfillment detection)\n   182→- Created `apps/platform/scripts/localnet-accounts/orao-treasury.json` — funded mock Orao treasury account\n   183→- Updated `apps/platform/scripts/localnet-bootstrap.sh` — added `--account` flags to pre-load all three Orao mock accounts at genesis\n   184→- Created `apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/localnet-setup.ts` — initializes coinflip and platform program configs (PDA creation via `initializeConfig`/`initializePlatform`) with deterministic admin/treasury keypairs; idempotent\n   185→- Created `apps/platform/e2e/local/lifecycle.spec.ts` — full lifecycle E2E test:\n   186→  - `beforeAll`: funds wallets + initializes program configs\n   187→  - Player A creates match (iron tier, HEADS) through UI\n   188→  - Player B navigates, sees match in lobby, joins through UI\n   189→  - Both players wait for VRF fulfillment detection (pre-loaded randomness → HEADS → creator wins)\n   190→  - Asserts Player A sees \"You Won!\", Player B sees \"You Lost\"\n   191→  - Player A claims payout through UI, returns to lobby\n   192→  - Console error tracking in both contexts\n   193→\n   194→**Design decisions**:\n   195→- Mock VRF resolution uses pre-loaded accounts at genesis (`--account` in bootstrap) rather than runtime account manipulation, since `solana-test-validator` doesn't expose a `setAccount` API like bankrun\n   196→- Orao random account data is 72 bytes: byte[0]=2 for program's `read_orao_randomness` (mock mode reads raw bytes 0-31), byte[8]=2 for frontend's `isVrfFulfilled` (reads bytes 8-72)\n   197→- Program configs initialized in test `beforeAll` (not bootstrap) because they require RPC transactions\n   198→- Player B navigates AFTER Player A creates match to avoid 30s lobby poll wait\n   199→- `PLAYER_A` always wins (deterministic randomness → HEADS → matches creator's side choice)\n   200→\n   201→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` (0 errors) + `pnpm typecheck` (pass) — all green.\n   202→\n   203→## Iteration 8 — 2026-02-26T11:40:55Z — OK\n   204→- **Log**: iteration-008.log\n   205→\n   206→## Iteration 9 — Local lifecycle on-chain assertions\n   207→\n   208→**Item**: Implement local lifecycle on-chain assertions (match state after create, closed after claim, fee + profile invariants)\n   209→\n   210→**Changes**:\n   211→- Updated `apps/platform/e2e/local/lifecycle.spec.ts` — added on-chain assertions to the lifecycle test:\n   212→  - After match creation: `assertMatchCreated()` verifies PDA state (waiting phase, correct creator, tier=0/iron, side=0/heads)\n   213→  - Before claim: snapshots treasury balance and both player profiles for delta comparison\n   214→  - After claim: `assertMatchClosed()` verifies match PDA is closed (no longer exists)\n   215→  - After claim: `assertTreasuryFee()` verifies treasury received expected 3% fee (floor(pool * 300 / 10000))\n   216→  - After claim: `assertPlayerProfileDelta()` for Player A (winner: +1 game, +1 win, wagered=5M lamports, won=payout)\n   217→  - After claim: `assertPlayerProfileDelta()` for Player B (loser: +1 game, +0 wins, wagered=5M lamports, won=0)\n   218→- Added `connection` fixture to test signature (from dual-context fixtures)\n   219→- Imported on-chain helpers + wallet keypairs\n   220→\n   221→**Design decisions**:\n   222→- Treasury address read from config PDA at runtime (`getTreasuryAddress()`) rather than importing static keypair — more robust\n   223→- Snapshots taken after join but before resolution/claim to capture clean pre-claim state\n   224→- Profile delta pattern (snapshot before + assert delta after) handles cases where profiles may or may not pre-exist\n   225→- Iron tier constants (tier=0, entry=5_000_000) match bankrun test definitions\n   226→\n   227→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` (0 errors) + `pnpm typecheck` (pass) — all green.\n   228→\n   229→## Iteration 9 — 2026-02-26T11:44:21Z — OK\n   230→- **Log**: iteration-009.log\n   231→\n   232→## Iteration 10 — Local cancel-flow test\n   233→\n   234→**Item**: Implement local cancel-flow test (create -> cancel -> refund verified -> lobby clears -> recreate works)\n   235→\n   236→**Changes**:\n   237→- Created `apps/platform/e2e/local/cancel-flow.spec.ts` — complete cancel flow E2E test\n   238→  - Player A creates a match (iron tier, heads), verifies active match in waiting state\n   239→  - On-chain: asserts match PDA exists in waiting phase via `assertMatchCreated()`\n   240→  - Player A cancels the match via `cancelMatch()` page-object helper\n   241→  - Asserts lobby is visible and empty (match cleared)\n   242→  - On-chain: asserts match PDA is closed via `assertMatchClosed()`\n   243→  - Balance verification: snapshots before create, after create, after cancel\n   244→    - Balance drops after create (entry + rent + tx fee)\n   245→    - Balance recovers after cancel (refund received)\n   246→    - Net cost < 0.01 SOL (only tx fees for create + cancel transactions)\n   247→  - Recreate: creates a new match (iron tier, tails) after cancellation — verifies same PDA can be reused\n   248→  - On-chain: asserts new match PDA exists with updated side (tails)\n   249→  - Cleanup: cancels second match to leave clean state\n   250→  - Console error tracking — no unhandled errors\n   251→\n   252→**Design decisions**:\n   253→- Single-player test (only Player A context needed; Player B fixtures unused)\n   254→- Balance delta assertion uses generous threshold (10M lamports / 0.01 SOL) for tx fee margin\n   255→- Second match uses different side (tails vs heads) to verify the PDA state is fresh\n   256→- Cleanup cancels the second match so subsequent test files start clean\n   257→\n   258→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` (0 errors) + `pnpm typecheck` (pass) — all green.\n   259→\n   260→## Iteration 10 — 2026-02-26T11:47:24Z — OK\n   261→- **Log**: iteration-010.log\n   262→\n   263→## Iteration 11 — Local error-flow tests\n   264→\n   265→**Item**: Implement local error-flow tests (insufficient balance, join locked match, loser claim attempt)\n   266→\n   267→**Changes**:\n   268→- Created `apps/platform/e2e/local/error-flow.spec.ts` — three error-flow E2E tests in a serial describe block:\n   269→  1. **Insufficient balance**: Funds Player A with 0.001 SOL (< iron tier entry 0.005 SOL), attempts to create match → asserts error toast with \"Insufficient balance\" text + verifies no match PDA created on-chain\n   270→  2. **Join unavailable match**: Player A creates match, Player B sees it in lobby, Player A cancels, Player B clicks stale join button → asserts error toast on B's page\n   271→  3. **Settle already-claimed match**: Full lifecycle (A creates, B joins, VRF resolves → A wins, A claims payout closing PDA), then Player B clicks \"Settle & Return\" on stale UI → asserts error toast on B's page\n   272→\n   273→**Design decisions**:\n   274→- Serial test execution (`test.describe.configure({ mode: 'serial' })`) — later tests depend on chain state from earlier ones (e.g., additional airdrop for test 2)\n   275→- Test 1 uses custom minimal funding (0.001 SOL) instead of `fundTestWallets()` to engineer insufficient balance\n   276→- Test 2 exploits the lobby poll interval (~30s) — after A cancels, B's stale match card is still clickable before the next poll\n   277→- Test 3 reuses the full lifecycle pattern from lifecycle.spec.ts with the additional step of B attempting to settle after A already claimed\n   278→- Error toast assertions use both specific text match (test 1: \"Insufficient balance\") and visibility-only (tests 2 & 3) for robustness\n   279→- No console error assertions for error-flow tests — transaction failure console errors are expected behavior\n   280→\n   281→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` (0 errors) + `pnpm typecheck` (pass) — all green.\n   282→\n   283→## Iteration 11 — 2026-02-26T12:05:00Z — OK\n   284→- **Log**: iteration-011.log\n   285→\n   286→## Iteration 11 — 2026-02-26T12:02:21Z — OK\n   287→- **Log**: iteration-011.log\n   288→\n   289→## Iteration 12 — Local suite command `pnpm test:e2e`\n   290→\n   291→**Item**: Add local suite command `pnpm test:e2e` that runs bootstrap -> tests -> teardown in one entrypoint\n   292→\n   293→**Changes**:\n   294→- Created `apps/platform/scripts/run-e2e-local.sh` — single-entrypoint wrapper script\n   295→  - Runs `localnet-bootstrap.sh` (fails fast if bootstrap fails, with cleanup)\n   296→  - Runs Playwright tests with `playwright.local.config.ts`\n   297→  - Always runs `localnet-teardown.sh` regardless of test outcome\n   298→  - Exits with the Playwright test exit code\n   299→- Updated `apps/platform/package.json` — added `test:e2e` script pointing to `run-e2e-local.sh`\n   300→- Updated root `package.json` — added `test:e2e` script using `pnpm --filter @rng-utopia/platform test:e2e`\n   301→\n   302→**Design decisions**:\n   303→- Shell wrapper (not npm chaining) for robust teardown-on-failure via exit code capture\n   304→- `set -euo pipefail` for strictness, but teardown runs unconditionally via `|| true`\n   305→- Root-level `pnpm test:e2e` delegates to platform package for single invocation from repo root\n   306→- Kept existing `test:e2e:local` script for running just Playwright (without bootstrap/teardown) during development\n   307→\n   308→**Verification**: `bash -n` (syntax OK) + `pnpm lint` (0 errors) + `pnpm typecheck` (pass) — all green.\n   309→\n   310→## Iteration 12 — 2026-02-26T12:04:33Z — OK\n   311→- **Log**: iteration-012.log\n   312→\n   313→## Iteration 13 — Devnet env contract (required vars + validation)\n   314→\n   315→**Item**: Add devnet env contract (required vars + validation): RPC URL, coinflip/platform program IDs, VRF config; fail fast if missing\n   316→\n   317→**Changes**:\n   318→- Created `apps/platform/e2e/devnet/helpers/env.ts` — devnet environment validation module\n   319→  - `DevnetConfig` interface: typed config with rpcUrl, network, coinflipProgramId, platformProgramId, oraoVrfProgramId\n   320→  - `validateDevnetEnv()` — reads + validates `VITE_RPC_URL`, `VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID`, `VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID` from process.env\n   321→    - Consolidated error reporting: collects all missing vars before throwing\n   322→    - Format validation: URL must be http(s), program IDs must be valid base58 Solana addresses\n   323→    - Optional with default: `VITE_SOLANA_NETWORK` defaults to \"devnet\"\n   324→    - Clear error message with hint about `.env.devnet`\n   325→  - `verifyDevnetDeployments(config)` — async RPC verification:\n   326→    1. RPC health check (getLatestBlockhash)\n   327→    2. Coinflip program exists and is executable\n   328→    3. Platform program exists and is executable\n   329→    4. Orao VRF program exists and is executable\n   330→    5. Orao VRF network state PDA exists (proves VRF initialized on cluster)\n   331→\n   332→**Design decisions**:\n   333→- Two-phase validation: sync env var check (`validateDevnetEnv`) + async deployment check (`verifyDevnetDeployments`) — sync phase is cheap and catches config errors before any RPC calls\n   334→- Orao VRF program ID is hardcoded (same address on all clusters) rather than configurable\n   335→- VRF network state PDA check validates the provider is actually initialized, not just deployed\n   336→- Module is importable from globalSetup or test beforeAll hooks\n   337→\n   338→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` (0 errors) + `pnpm typecheck` (pass) — all green.\n   339→\n   340→## Iteration 13 — 2026-02-26T12:08:35Z — OK\n   341→- **Log**: iteration-013.log\n   342→\n   343→## Iteration 14 — Dedicated devnet E2E Playwright project/config\n   344→\n   345→**Item**: Add dedicated devnet E2E Playwright project/config (`e2e/devnet/**`) that does not run local bootstrap/deploy\n   346→\n   347→**Changes**:\n   348→- Created `apps/platform/playwright.devnet.config.ts` — dedicated Playwright config for devnet E2E tests\n   349→  - Runs on port 3003 (separate from local:3002, real:3001, visual:3000)\n   350→  - 120-second timeout (longer for real VRF fulfillment)\n   351→  - `VITE_MOCK_MODE=false`, `VITE_TEST_WALLET=true`\n   352→  - RPC URL and program IDs inherited from process.env (NOT hardcoded)\n   353→  - Tests match `devnet/**/*.spec.ts`\n   354→  - No local bootstrap/deploy — does not start validator or deploy programs\n   355→- Created `apps/platform/e2e/devnet/fixtures.ts` — devnet-specific dual-player fixtures\n   356→  - Same isolated dual-context pattern as local fixtures\n   357→  - `devnetConfig` fixture validates env vars via `validateDevnetEnv()`\n   358→  - `connection` fixture connects to devnet RPC URL from config\n   359→  - Reuses deterministic keypairs from `wallets.ts`\n   360→- Created `apps/platform/e2e/devnet/smoke.spec.ts` — devnet smoke test\n   361→  - Verifies devnet deployments (RPC health, program existence, VRF initialized)\n   362→  - Verifies app loads against devnet (React renders, navigation visible)\n   363→  - Verifies wallet connects with test keypair (pubkey visible in UI)\n   364→\n   365→**Design decisions**:\n   366→- Separate config file (not a project inside local config) to fully decouple devnet from local validator lifecycle\n   367→- Env vars not hardcoded in config — must be set before running (or via .env file) — enforced by env.ts validation\n   368→- Port 3003 avoids conflict with all other Playwright configs\n   369→- Longer timeout (120s vs 60s) accounts for real VRF fulfillment latency\n   370→- Devnet fixtures expose `devnetConfig` so lifecycle tests can access program IDs for on-chain assertions\n   371→\n   372→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` (0 errors) + `pnpm typecheck` (pass) — all green.\n   373→\n   374→## Iteration 14 — 2026-02-26T12:11:39Z — OK\n   375→- **Log**: iteration-014.log\n   376→\n   377→## Iteration 15 — Devnet lifecycle test (real VRF)\n   378→\n   379→**Item**: Implement devnet lifecycle test using deployed contracts + real VRF request/fulfillment path (no mock resolve shortcut)\n   380→\n   381→**Changes**:\n   382→- Created `apps/platform/e2e/devnet/lifecycle.spec.ts` — full devnet lifecycle E2E test\n   383→  - `beforeAll`: validates devnet env, funds wallets via airdrop if balance < 0.1 SOL (with retry for rate limits)\n   384→  - Player A creates match (iron tier, heads) through UI\n   385→  - Player B navigates, sees match in lobby, joins through UI\n   386→  - Both players wait for real VRF fulfillment (90s timeout — no mock shortcut)\n   387→  - Non-deterministic outcome handling: test determines winner/loser from UI result classes\n   388→  - Winner claims payout, verifies \"Back to Lobby\" button\n   389→  - Loser settles and returns to lobby\n   390→  - Console error tracking in both contexts\n   391→\n   392→**Design decisions**:\n   393→- Non-deterministic winner: real VRF means either player can win — test branches on `waitForResult()` outcome\n   394→- `ensureFunded()` helper checks existing balance before airdrop (avoids unnecessary rate-limited requests)\n   395→- Airdrop retry (2 attempts with 2s delay) handles transient devnet rate limits\n   396→- 90s VRF timeout accounts for slower devnet fulfillment (typical: 10-30s)\n   397→- Uses `validateDevnetEnv()` directly in `beforeAll` (not fixture) since `beforeAll` is worker-scoped\n   398→- Imports page-objects from `../local/helpers/` (shared across suites)\n   399→- On-chain assertions deferred to next checklist item\n   400→\n   401→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` (0 errors) + `pnpm typecheck` (pass) — all green.\n   402→\n   403→## Iteration 15 — 2026-02-26T12:16:30Z — OK\n   404→- **Log**: iteration-015.log\n   405→\n   406→## Iteration 16 — Robust VRF fulfillment polling + tx signature logging\n   407→\n   408→**Item**: Add robust fulfillment polling/backoff + timeout budget in devnet test, with tx signature logging for failures\n   409→\n   410→**Changes**:\n   411→- Created `apps/platform/e2e/devnet/helpers/vrf-polling.ts` — VRF fulfillment polling module\n   412→  - `pollVrfFulfillment(connection, creator, timeoutMs)` — polls match PDA with exponential backoff (2s → 10s max, 1.5x factor)\n   413→  - Logs timeout budget at each attempt: `[vrf-poll] Attempt N: phase=\"locked\" [12.3s / 90.0s, 14% budget]`\n   414→  - On timeout: collects and logs transaction signatures on match PDA for diagnostics\n   415→  - `VrfTimeoutError` with `elapsedMs`, `attempts`, `lastPhase`, `signatures` properties\n   416→  - `collectMatchSignatures()` — fetches recent signatures via `getSignaturesForAddress`\n   417→  - `logRecentSignatures(connection, address, label)` — diagnostic helper for post-test tx logging\n   418→- Updated `apps/platform/e2e/devnet/lifecycle.spec.ts` — integrated robust polling\n   419→  - Dual-strategy VRF wait: on-chain poll (`pollVrfFulfillment`) + UI result wait (`po.waitForResult`) in parallel\n   420→  - On-chain poll failure doesn't fail the test (UI detection is the primary assertion)\n   421→  - Post-test: logs recent transaction signatures for both players (diagnostic artifact)\n   422→\n   423→**Design decisions**:\n   424→- Exponential backoff (2s → 3s → 4.5s → 6.75s → 10s cap) avoids hammering devnet RPC\n   425→- Dual-strategy (on-chain + UI) provides redundancy — on-chain poll often detects fulfillment before UI poll cycle\n   426→- Transaction signatures logged on both success and timeout for full debuggability\n   427→- `VrfTimeoutError` extends Error with structured diagnostic fields for programmatic handling\n   428→\n   429→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` (0 errors) + `pnpm typecheck` (pass) — all green.\n   430→\n   431→## Iteration 16 — 2026-02-26T12:22:03Z — OK\n   432→- **Log**: iteration-016.log\n   433→\n   434→## Iteration 17 — Devnet on-chain assertions\n   435→\n   436→**Item**: Add devnet on-chain assertions for payout, fee transfer, and final match/account state\n   437→\n   438→**Changes**:\n   439→- Updated `apps/platform/e2e/devnet/lifecycle.spec.ts` — added comprehensive on-chain assertions\n   440→  - After match creation: `assertMatchCreated()` verifies PDA state (waiting phase, correct creator, tier=0/iron, side=0/heads)\n   441→  - After join: snapshots treasury balance and both player profiles for delta comparison\n   442→  - After claim: `assertMatchClosed()` verifies match PDA is closed\n   443→  - After claim: `assertTreasuryFee()` verifies treasury received expected 3% fee\n   444→  - After claim: `assertPlayerProfileDelta()` for winner (+1 game, +1 win, wagered=ENTRY_AMOUNT, won=payout)\n   445→  - After claim: `assertPlayerProfileDelta()` for loser (+1 game, +0 wins, wagered=ENTRY_AMOUNT, won=0)\n   446→  - Added on-chain constants: TIER_IRON, SIDE_HEADS, ENTRY_AMOUNT\n   447→  - Imported on-chain helpers from `../local/helpers/on-chain` (reused, not duplicated)\n   448→\n   449→**Design decisions**:\n   450→- Non-deterministic winner handling: uses `resultA` (\"won\"/\"lost\") to determine which player's keypair and profile snapshot to use for winner/loser assertions\n   451→- Snapshots taken after join but before VRF resolution to capture clean pre-claim state\n   452→- Treasury address read from config PDA at runtime (`getTreasuryAddress()`)\n   453→- Reuses existing on-chain assertion helpers from local suite (no code duplication)\n   454→- Console logging at each on-chain assertion step for diagnostic artifact trail\n   455→\n   456→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` (0 errors) + `pnpm typecheck` (pass) — all green.\n   457→\n   458→## Iteration 17 — 2026-02-26T12:30:00Z — OK\n   459→- **Log**: iteration-017.log\n   460→\n   461→## Iteration 17 — 2026-02-26T12:25:17Z — OK\n   462→- **Log**: iteration-017.log\n   463→\n   464→## Iteration 18 — Devnet suite command `pnpm test:e2e:devnet`\n   465→\n   466→**Item**: Add devnet suite command `pnpm test:e2e:devnet` wired to the devnet project/config\n   467→\n   468→**Changes**:\n   469→- Created `apps/platform/scripts/run-e2e-devnet.sh` — single-entrypoint wrapper script for devnet E2E tests\n   470→  - Fast-fail env validation: checks `VITE_RPC_URL`, `VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID`, `VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID` before starting Vite\n   471→  - Logs config summary (RPC URL, program IDs, network) for diagnostics\n   472→  - Runs Playwright with `playwright.devnet.config.ts`\n   473→  - No bootstrap/teardown — devnet uses pre-deployed contracts\n   474→- Updated `apps/platform/package.json` — added `test:e2e:devnet` script pointing to `run-e2e-devnet.sh`\n   475→- Updated root `package.json` — added `test:e2e:devnet` script using `pnpm --filter @rng-utopia/platform test:e2e:devnet`\n   476→\n   477→**Design decisions**:\n   478→- Shell-level env validation (before Playwright/Vite launch) gives immediate, clear error messages vs. cryptic failures mid-test\n   479→- Simpler than local wrapper (no bootstrap/teardown) since devnet contracts are pre-deployed\n   480→- Root-level `pnpm test:e2e:devnet` delegates to platform package for single invocation from repo root\n   481→\n   482→**Verification**: `bash -n` (syntax OK) + `pnpm lint` (0 errors) + `pnpm typecheck` (pass) — all green.\n   483→\n   484→## Iteration 18 — 2026-02-26T12:35:00Z — OK\n   485→- **Log**: iteration-018.log\n   486→\n   487→## Iteration 18 — 2026-02-26T12:27:00Z — OK\n   488→- **Log**: iteration-018.log\n   489→\n   490→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2ba24589-b147-45b6-b7a4-325b1a39ca4a","uuid":"d29a9e4a-545c-4a4f-9b3c-580b4e711767","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/203-e2e-integration/history.md","content":"# Implementation History — 203-e2e-integration\n\nIteration log for the autonomous spec loop. Each entry records what was\nattempted and whether it succeeded. The agent reads this file at the start\nof every iteration to understand prior context.\n\n---\n\n## Iteration 1 — Local E2E Playwright config + directory\n\n**Item**: Add dedicated local E2E Playwright project/config (`e2e/local/**`)\n\n**Changes**:\n- Created `apps/platform/playwright.local.config.ts` — new config for local E2E tests (port 3002, `VITE_MOCK_MODE=false`, `VITE_RPC_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8899`)\n- Updated `apps/platform/playwright.config.ts` — added `testMatch: \"visual/**/*.spec.ts\"` to prevent default config from running local tests\n- Created `apps/platform/e2e/local/smoke.spec.ts` — smoke test verifying app loads in real mode\n- Added `test:e2e:local` script to `apps/platform/package.json`\n\n**Verification**: `pnpm lint` (0 errors) + `pnpm typecheck` (pass) — all green.\n\n## Iteration 1 — 2026-02-26T10:52:11Z — OK\n- **Log**: iteration-001.log\n\n## Iteration 2 — Localnet bootstrap script\n\n**Item**: Create localnet bootstrap script: start fresh `solana-test-validator`, deploy coinflip + platform programs, wait for RPC readiness\n\n**Changes**:\n- Created `apps/platform/scripts/localnet-bootstrap.sh` — starts fresh `solana-test-validator` with programs preloaded via `--bpf-program`, waits for RPC readiness, writes PID file for teardown\n- Updated `.devcontainer/devcontainer.json` — added `--security-opt=seccomp=unconfined` to `runArgs` (required for Solana 3.x io_uring)\n- Updated `.gitignore` — added `.localnet-ledger/` and `.localnet.pid`\n\n**Key design decisions**:\n- Uses `--bpf-program` to preload programs at genesis (faster than post-start deploy)\n- Writes PID to `.localnet.pid` for teardown script to consume\n- Includes io_uring preflight check with clear error message pointing to seccomp fix\n- Kills any existing validator (by PID file or port 8899) before starting fresh\n\n**Note**: `solana-test-validator` requires `io_uring` syscall (Solana 3.x). Docker blocks it by default. The devcontainer fix (`seccomp=unconfined`) requires container rebuild to take effect. Script cannot be fully tested in the current session but syntax validates (`bash -n`) and all logic is sound.\n\n**Verification**: `bash -n` (syntax OK) + `pnpm lint` (0 errors) — all green.\n\n## Iteration 2 — 2026-02-26T11:00:00Z — OK\n- **Log**: iteration-002.log\n\n## Iteration 3 — Localnet teardown script\n\n**Item**: Create localnet teardown script: stop validator process, clean temp ledger/logs, and guarantee cleanup on test failure\n\n**Changes**:\n- Created `apps/platform/scripts/localnet-teardown.sh` — counterpart to `localnet-bootstrap.sh`\n  - Reads PID from `.localnet.pid` and sends SIGTERM, waits up to 5s, then SIGKILL if needed\n  - Kills any stray process on port 8899 (safety net)\n  - Removes `.localnet-ledger/` directory and `.localnet-validator.log`\n  - `--keep-logs` flag to preserve log file for debugging\n  - Idempotent: safe to call multiple times or when nothing is running\n\n**Verification**: `bash -n` (syntax OK) + `pnpm lint` (0 errors) — all green.\n\n## Iteration 3 — 2026-02-26T11:10:00Z — OK\n- **Log**: iteration-003.log\n\n## Iteration 3 — 2026-02-26T11:01:27Z — OK\n- **Log**: iteration-003.log\n\n## Iteration 4 — Deterministic wallet-funding helper\n\n**Item**: Add deterministic wallet-funding helper (airdrop + confirm) for both test players before each local suite run\n\n**Changes**:\n- Created `apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/wallets.ts` — wallet funding helper for local E2E tests\n  - Deterministic keypairs: `PLAYER_A` (seed 0xaa×32) and `PLAYER_B` (seed 0xbb×32) via `Keypair.fromSeed()`\n  - `fundWallet(connection, pubkey, sol)` — airdrops SOL and confirms transaction\n  - `fundTestWallets(rpcUrl, sol)` — funds both players in parallel, sanity-checks balances\n  - Default: 10 SOL per player on `http://127.0.0.1:8899`\n\n**Design decisions**:\n- Fixed seeds (not random) ensure identical keypairs across runs for determinism\n- Parallel airdrop via `Promise.all` for faster setup\n- Post-airdrop balance assertions catch silent RPC failures early\n- Helper is importable from any test file (`beforeAll` or global setup)\n\n**Verification**: `pnpm lint` (0 errors) + `pnpm typecheck` (pass) — all green.\n\n## Iteration 4 — 2026-02-26T11:05:14Z — OK\n- **Log**: iteration-004.log\n\n## Iteration 5 — Shared E2E page-object helpers\n\n**Item**: Add shared E2E helpers: selectors/page-object methods for create, join, claim, cancel, and reusable wait/assert primitives\n\n**Changes**:\n- Created `apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/page-objects.ts` — comprehensive E2E helper module\n  - `sel` object: CSS-class-based selectors for all coinflip UI elements (sidebar, lobby, match cards, active match, results, errors)\n  - Page-object actions: `navigateToCoinflip()`, `selectTier()`, `selectSide()`, `createMatch()`, `joinMatch()`, `cancelMatch()`, `claimOrSettle()`, `backToLobby()`\n  - Wait primitives: `waitForPhaseLabel()`, `waitForResult()`, `waitForLobbyMatch()`, `waitForLobby()`, `waitForText()`\n  - Assert primitives: `assertLobbyEmpty()`, `assertErrorToast()`, `assertNoErrorToast()`\n  - Utility: `getSolBalance()` (RPC-based, via page.evaluate), `trackConsoleErrors()` (collector + assertClean)\n\n**Design decisions**:\n- CSS-class selectors (no data-testid needed — matches existing component markup)\n- All actions include built-in waits for state transitions (e.g., createMatch waits for active match view)\n- `claimOrSettle()` handles both winner (Claim Payout) and loser (Settle & Return) since both use the sidebar button\n- `getSolBalance()` uses page.evaluate + JSON-RPC for balance checks from within test context\n- `trackConsoleErrors()` filters known browser noise (favicon, fonts, third-party cookies)\n\n**Verification**: `pnpm lint` (0 errors) + `pnpm typecheck` (pass) — all green.\n\n## Iteration 5 — 2026-02-26T11:15:00Z — OK\n- **Log**: iteration-005.log\n\n## Iteration 5 — 2026-02-26T11:09:56Z — OK\n- **Log**: iteration-005.log\n\n## Iteration 6 — Shared on-chain assertion helpers\n\n**Item**: Add shared on-chain assertion helpers for match PDA state, treasury fee delta, and player profile stat updates\n\n**Changes**:\n- Created `apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/on-chain.ts` — comprehensive on-chain assertion module\n  - PDA derivation: `getMatchPda()`, `getConfigPda()`, `getPlayerProfilePda()`\n  - Program instances: `getCoinflipProgram()`, `getPlatformProgram()` (read-only Anchor providers)\n  - Fetch helpers: `fetchMatch()`, `fetchPlayerProfile()`, `getTreasuryAddress()`\n  - Balance helpers: `getBalanceLamports()`, `snapshotBalance()`\n  - Fee calculation: `calculateExpectedFee()` — mirrors on-chain floor(pool * 300 / 10000) logic\n  - Match assertions: `assertMatchCreated()` (verifies waiting phase, creator, tier, side), `assertMatchClosed()` (verifies PDA no longer exists)\n  - Treasury assertions: `assertTreasuryFee()` — compares balance delta against expected fee\n  - Profile assertions: `assertPlayerProfile()`, `assertPlayerProfileDelta()`, `snapshotPlayerProfile()`\n\n**Design decisions**:\n- Uses `@rng-utopia/anchor-client` IDLs for account deserialization (same as production code)\n- Program IDs derived from IDL `.address` field (single source of truth)\n- Read-only AnchorProvider with empty wallet (no signing needed for queries)\n- Snapshot/delta pattern for treasury and profile assertions (capture before, assert delta after)\n- Null-safe fetches: returns null for closed/missing accounts instead of throwing\n- TypeScript interfaces for MatchAccount and PlayerProfileAccount mirror on-chain struct shapes\n\n**Verification**: `pnpm lint` (0 errors) + `pnpm typecheck` (pass) — all green.\n\n## Iteration 6 — 2026-02-26T11:15:31Z — OK\n- **Log**: iteration-006.log\n\n## Iteration 7 — Dual-browser-context fixture\n\n**Item**: Add dual-browser-context fixture with isolated storage/session for player A and player B\n\n**Changes**:\n- Created `packages/wallet/src/test/TestWalletWrapper.tsx` — bridge component that reads a 32-byte seed from `window.__TEST_WALLET_SEED__` and renders `TestWalletProvider` with the corresponding `Keypair`\n- Modified `packages/wallet/src/WalletProvider.tsx` — added test wallet mode:\n  - New `isTestWalletMode()` function checks `VITE_TEST_WALLET` env var\n  - Lazy-loads `TestWalletWrapper` when `VITE_TEST_WALLET=true`\n  - Mode priority: mock > test > real\n- Created `apps/platform/e2e/local/fixtures.ts` — dual-browser-context Playwright fixture:\n  - `playerAContext` / `playerBContext`: isolated browser contexts with keypair seed injected via `addInitScript`\n  - `playerAPage` / `playerBPage`: ready-to-use Page instances within each context\n  - `playerAKeypair` / `playerBKeypair`: deterministic keypairs from `wallets.ts`\n  - `connection`: shared RPC connection to the local validator\n  - Exports extended `test` and `expect` for use in lifecycle tests\n- Updated `apps/platform/playwright.local.config.ts` — added `VITE_TEST_WALLET: \"true\"` env var\n\n**Design decisions**:\n- Keypair injection via `context.addInitScript()` runs before any page script, ensuring the seed is available when React renders `WalletProvider`\n- `TestWalletWrapper` is lazy-loaded to keep the bundle clean in non-test modes\n- Each context is fully isolated (separate storage, cookies, sessions) — no cross-contamination between players\n- The `createPlayerContext()` helper extracts the 32-byte seed from `keypair.secretKey.slice(0, 32)` and passes it as a plain array (serialisable across the Playwright boundary)\n\n**Verification**: `pnpm lint` (0 errors) + `pnpm typecheck` (pass) — all green.\n\n## Iteration 7 — 2026-02-26T11:25:00Z — OK\n- **Log**: iteration-007.log\n\n## Iteration 7 — 2026-02-26T11:22:53Z — OK\n- **Log**: iteration-007.log\n\n## Iteration 8 — Local lifecycle test (create → join → resolve → claim)\n\n**Item**: Implement local lifecycle test (create -> join -> resolve programmatically -> claim) with UI assertions in both contexts\n\n**Changes**:\n- Created `apps/platform/scripts/localnet-accounts/orao-network-state.json` — mock Orao VRF network state PDA with deterministic treasury address at offset 40 (required by `buildJoinMatchTx`)\n- Created `apps/platform/scripts/localnet-accounts/orao-random-player-a.json` — pre-fulfilled mock VRF randomness account for Player A's match PDA (byte[0]=2→HEADS, byte[8]=2→frontend fulfillment detection)\n- Created `apps/platform/scripts/localnet-accounts/orao-treasury.json` — funded mock Orao treasury account\n- Updated `apps/platform/scripts/localnet-bootstrap.sh` — added `--account` flags to pre-load all three Orao mock accounts at genesis\n- Created `apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/localnet-setup.ts` — initializes coinflip and platform program configs (PDA creation via `initializeConfig`/`initializePlatform`) with deterministic admin/treasury keypairs; idempotent\n- Created `apps/platform/e2e/local/lifecycle.spec.ts` — full lifecycle E2E test:\n  - `beforeAll`: funds wallets + initializes program configs\n  - Player A creates match (iron tier, HEADS) through UI\n  - Player B navigates, sees match in lobby, joins through UI\n  - Both players wait for VRF fulfillment detection (pre-loaded randomness → HEADS → creator wins)\n  - Asserts Player A sees \"You Won!\", Player B sees \"You Lost\"\n  - Player A claims payout through UI, returns to lobby\n  - Console error tracking in both contexts\n\n**Design decisions**:\n- Mock VRF resolution uses pre-loaded accounts at genesis (`--account` in bootstrap) rather than runtime account manipulation, since `solana-test-validator` doesn't expose a `setAccount` API like bankrun\n- Orao random account data is 72 bytes: byte[0]=2 for program's `read_orao_randomness` (mock mode reads raw bytes 0-31), byte[8]=2 for frontend's `isVrfFulfilled` (reads bytes 8-72)\n- Program configs initialized in test `beforeAll` (not bootstrap) because they require RPC transactions\n- Player B navigates AFTER Player A creates match to avoid 30s lobby poll wait\n- `PLAYER_A` always wins (deterministic randomness → HEADS → matches creator's side choice)\n\n**Verification**: `pnpm lint` (0 errors) + `pnpm typecheck` (pass) — all green.\n\n## Iteration 8 — 2026-02-26T11:40:55Z — OK\n- **Log**: iteration-008.log\n\n## Iteration 9 — Local lifecycle on-chain assertions\n\n**Item**: Implement local lifecycle on-chain assertions (match state after create, closed after claim, fee + profile invariants)\n\n**Changes**:\n- Updated `apps/platform/e2e/local/lifecycle.spec.ts` — added on-chain assertions to the lifecycle test:\n  - After match creation: `assertMatchCreated()` verifies PDA state (waiting phase, correct creator, tier=0/iron, side=0/heads)\n  - Before claim: snapshots treasury balance and both player profiles for delta comparison\n  - After claim: `assertMatchClosed()` verifies match PDA is closed (no longer exists)\n  - After claim: `assertTreasuryFee()` verifies treasury received expected 3% fee (floor(pool * 300 / 10000))\n  - After claim: `assertPlayerProfileDelta()` for Player A (winner: +1 game, +1 win, wagered=5M lamports, won=payout)\n  - After claim: `assertPlayerProfileDelta()` for Player B (loser: +1 game, +0 wins, wagered=5M lamports, won=0)\n- Added `connection` fixture to test signature (from dual-context fixtures)\n- Imported on-chain helpers + wallet keypairs\n\n**Design decisions**:\n- Treasury address read from config PDA at runtime (`getTreasuryAddress()`) rather than importing static keypair — more robust\n- Snapshots taken after join but before resolution/claim to capture clean pre-claim state\n- Profile delta pattern (snapshot before + assert delta after) handles cases where profiles may or may not pre-exist\n- Iron tier constants (tier=0, entry=5_000_000) match bankrun test definitions\n\n**Verification**: `pnpm lint` (0 errors) + `pnpm typecheck` (pass) — all green.\n\n## Iteration 9 — 2026-02-26T11:44:21Z — OK\n- **Log**: iteration-009.log\n\n## Iteration 10 — Local cancel-flow test\n\n**Item**: Implement local cancel-flow test (create -> cancel -> refund verified -> lobby clears -> recreate works)\n\n**Changes**:\n- Created `apps/platform/e2e/local/cancel-flow.spec.ts` — complete cancel flow E2E test\n  - Player A creates a match (iron tier, heads), verifies active match in waiting state\n  - On-chain: asserts match PDA exists in waiting phase via `assertMatchCreated()`\n  - Player A cancels the match via `cancelMatch()` page